H0.text: If you were from the Cayman Islands, which is part of the British West Indies, what sort of passport would you have. Caymanian

H1.text: If you were from the Cayman Islands, which is part of the British West Indies, what sort of passport would you have. West Indian

H2.text: If you were from the Cayman Islands, which is part of the British West Indies, what sort of passport would you have. Caribbean

H3.text: If you were from the Cayman Islands, which is part of the British West Indies, what sort of passport would you have. Britsih

A4.text: Cayman Islands passports are a variant of the British passport which are issued to British Overseas Territories Citizens connected to the Cayman Islands.

A5.text: Since 2016, all Caymanian passports are issued in the United Kingdom by His Majesty's Passport Office (HMPO).
